A woman carrying goods enters the Beitbridge border near Musina. JOHANNESBURG - Parliamentary committees will on Saturday inspect the multimillion-rand Beitbridge border fence. The fence was erected as part of efforts to fight COVID-19. READ: Beitbridge border fence project riddled with corruption, probe finds But an investigation found misconduct in its procurement and construction. The investigation also revealed the inferior quality of the fence. Fourteen officials are facing misconduct charges related to the project.